Section A: Core JOIN Fundamentals (Warm-up)
Q1. List all orders with:
customer name
product name
order date
quantity
(INNER JOIN across all three tables)

Q2. Display all customers and their orders (if any).
Include customers who have never placed an order.

Q3. Find all products that have never been ordered.

Q4. Show total number of orders per customer
(include customers with zero orders).
(LEFT JOIN + GROUP BY)

Q5. List all orders placed by customers from India, along with product names.
(JOIN + WHERE)

Section B: Business-Style JOIN Analysis (Medium)
Q6. Calculate the total revenue generated by each customer
(revenue = price × quantity).
(3-table JOIN + aggregation)

Q7. Find the top 5 customers by total spending.
(JOIN + SUM + ORDER BY)

Q8. Show the total quantity sold for each product category.
(JOIN + GROUP BY)

Q9. List all orders where the product price is greater than ₹20,000.
(JOIN + condition on products)

Q10. Find customers who have ordered more than one distinct product.
(JOIN + COUNT DISTINCT)

Section C: OUTER JOIN & Edge Cases (Advanced)
Q11. Find customers who placed exactly one order.
(JOIN + GROUP BY + HAVING)

Q12. Display each product along with:
total quantity sold
show 0 for products never ordered
(LEFT JOIN + COALESCE)

Q13. Find the country-wise total revenue, including countries with no orders.
(LEFT JOIN from customers)

Section D: Interview-Level JOIN Challenges (Hard)
Q14. Find the most frequently ordered product
(based on total quantity sold).
(JOIN + aggregation + ranking logic)

Q15. Identify customers who have never ordered Electronics category products.
(JOIN + anti-join logic)